column6: Opening
I’ve been feeling off lately—just tired and achy all over. Not sure what’s wrong.
I don’t have energy like usual. Everything feels sluggish—no specific pain, just unwell.
My baby has been fussier than usual and doesn’t seem herself—no fever, just not right.
I feel run down—no fever or cough, just weak and not myself for days now.
I’ve been feeling weird—dizzy and tired, but no obvious illness. Just not normal.
My son has been low-energy and cranky—no fever, but something seems off.
I feel generally unwell—no specific symptoms, just a constant blah feeling.
My son says he feels ‘funny’—no pain, just not right for a few days.
I’ve had this lingering fatigue and mild nausea—nothing severe, but it’s persistent.
My baby isn’t eating as much and seems extra sleepy—no fever, but I’m worried.

I’ve been feeling really off for the past week—just exhausted all the time, even after sleeping. I don’t have a fever, but I’ve been getting random headaches and my appetite is gone. It’s like my body is drained, and I can’t pinpoint why. Could this be stress or something else?

Lately, I’ve been feeling run down—no energy, no motivation. I’ve had some mild nausea here and there, and my muscles ache like I’ve been working out, but I haven’t. No fever or cough, just this constant foggy feeling. Is this just aging, or should I be concerned?

My baby has been unusually fussy for days—not feeding as well, sleeping more than usual, and just seems ‘off.’ No fever or rash, but she’s not her usual self. I’m worried because she’s so little—could this be an infection or just a phase?

I’ve been feeling weak and unsteady for about two weeks now. No specific pain, but I’m dizzy at times and just don’t have my usual stamina. My appetite is lower, and I’ve lost a couple of pounds without trying. At my age, I’m worried—could this be something serious?

I’ve been feeling really weird lately—just not myself. Super tired, a bit lightheaded, and my stomach feels off, but no vomiting or diarrhea. I’ve also been super irritable, which isn’t normal for me. Could this be hormonal, or should I get checked for something else?

My son has been complaining about feeling ‘yucky’ for days—no fever, but he’s pale, not eating much, and says his body feels heavy. He’s usually active, but now he just wants to lie around. Should I bring him in, or is this just a passing bug?

I’ve been feeling generally unwell for over a week—no energy, occasional chills, and just a sense of being ‘off.’ My joints ache a little, but no swelling. I thought it might be menopause-related, but it’s dragging on. Could this be my thyroid or something else?

My toddler has been clingy and lethargic for three days—no fever, but he’s not eating well and seems more tired than usual. He’s also been whining about his tummy but no vomiting. Is this just a virus, or should I be worried about something more?

I’ve had this lingering fatigue and brain fog for weeks—no fever, but I feel like I’m moving through molasses. My sleep is disrupted, and I’ve had mild nausea on and off. I thought it was burnout, but it’s not improving. Could this be anemia or a vitamin deficiency?

My son has been complaining of feeling ‘blah’—no fever, but he’s lost interest in playing, says his head hurts sometimes, and just looks pale. He’s not eating much and seems more tired than usual after school. Is this just growing pains, or should we see a doctor?
